<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN220-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. avaṉ vaṭakkiruntāṉaiyuḻaic ceṉṟu mīṇṭuvantu uṟaiyūrkaṇṭa potatiyār aḻutu pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN220">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>peruñcōṟu payantu palyāṇṭu puranta</l>
<l>peruṅkaḷi ṟiḻanta paitaṟ pāka</l>
<l>ṉatucērn talkiya vaḻuṅka lālai</l>
<l>veḷilpā ḻākka kaṇṭukaluḻn tāṅkuk</l>
<l>kalaṅkiṉe ṉallaṉō yāṉē polantārt</l>
<l>tērvaṇ kiḷḷi pōkiya</l>
<l>pēricai mūtūr maṉṟaṅ kaṇṭē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>A suffering mahout who has lost a big elephant bull (2)</l>
<l>he had protected for many years, pouring [it] great rice, (1)</l>
<l>weeping like [him] when seeing that the post is in ruin (4)</l>
<l>in the noisy stables where it had rested joined to it, (3)  </l>
<l>was I not upset, I, (5a-c)</l>
<l>when seeing the central place of the famous ancient town (7)</l>
<l>from which Kiḷḷi, generous with chariots [and] golden garlands, went [away]? (5d-6)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
